},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"571e95",
"children":[
"Chronic cough lasts ≥8 weeks. Upper airways cough syndrome (UACS) caused by postnasal drip, asthma, and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastroesophageal reflux disease",
"children":[
"GERD"
]
},
" are responsible for approximately 90% of cases of chronic cough but are responsible for 99% in patients who are nonsmokers, have a normal chest x-ray, and are not taking an ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin-converting enzyme",
"children":[
"ACE"
]
},
" inhibitor."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c76e4b",
"children":[
"All patients should undergo chest x-ray. Smoking cessation and discontinuation of ACE inhibitors are indicated for 4 weeks before additional evaluation."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s3_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f4b2fd",
"children":[
"If a cause is not determined after initial evaluation, a stepwise approach is pursued, beginning with a 2-week trial of empiric treatment for ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"upper airways cough syndrome",
"children":[
"UACS"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
},
